<p>The <b>Eurasian bittern</b> or <b>great bittern</b> (<i>Botaurus stellaris</i>) is a wading <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heron" title="Heron">heron</a> family <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ardeidae" title="Ardeidae" class="mw-redirect">Ardeidae</a>. It is one of the species to which the <i>Agreement on the Conservation of African-Eurasian Migratory Waterbirds</i> (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AEWA" title="AEWA" class="mw-redirect">AEWA</a>) applies.</p>
<p></p>
